## ğŸ“Œ Overview

This project uses **YOLOv5** to detect, track, and alert when a baby moves outside a **predefined safety zone**.
It supports:

* ğŸ¥ **Real-time webcam monitoring**
* ğŸ“‚ **Custom/local videos**
* ğŸ“º **YouTube videos**

**Goal**: Create a smart monitoring system for nurseries or research projects.

---

## ğŸš€ Features

* âœ… **Baby Detection** â€” Trained YOLOv5 model to detect babies in frames.
* âœ… **Tracking** â€” Continuous tracking with bounding boxes.
* âœ… **Safety Zone** â€” Virtual zone to ensure the baby stays safe.
* âœ… **Alert System** â€” Visual warnings for unsafe positions.
* âœ… **YouTube Integration** â€” Process videos directly from YouTube links.
* âœ… **Colab-Friendly** â€” Runs without local GPU.

---

## ğŸ›  Tech Stack

| Tool/Library | Purpose                   |
| ------------ | ------------------------- |
| **Python 3** | Main programming language |
| **YOLOv5**   | Object detection          |
| **PyTorch**  | Deep learning framework   |
| **OpenCV**   | Video & image processing  |
| **yt-dlp**   | YouTube video downloading |
| **Pygame**   | Sound alerts (local runs) |

---

## ğŸ“‚ Dataset

* **Source**: Custom dataset via [Roboflow](https://roboflow.com)
* **Size**: 2,000+ annotated baby images
* **Format**: YOLO TXT labels
* **Classes**:

```
0 baby
```

